  "response": "You can find the audiobook of \"Beowulf\" translated by Burton Raffel on various platforms:\n\n1. **Amazon Audible** - Audible often carries a wide range of audiobooks, including classics like \"Beowulf\". You can check their website or app.\n\n2. **Apple Books** - If you use an Apple device, you may find the audiobook available on Apple Books.\n\n3. **Google Play Books** - Google Play also has a large selection of audiobooks and might carry \"Beowulf\".\n\n4. **Libby or OverDrive** - If you have a library card, you can check if your local library offers the audiobook through apps like Libby or OverDrive.\n\n5. **Audiobook retail sites** - Websites like audiobooks.com or audiobookstore.com often have a wide selection including literary classics.\n\n6. **YouTube or other free sources** - Sometimes, older works like \"Beowulf\" might be available for free on YouTube or sites dedicated to free audiobooks, though the quality and legality can vary.\n\nBe sure to check the specific format and narration options to find the one that best suits your preference!",
